es (1.961 km) of it is land and 0.002 square miles (0.005 km) of water (0.26%) is water. Robbinsville CDP and Robbinsville Township are not coextensive, with the CDP covering 3.7% of the of the township as a whole. Robbinsville (CDP), New Jersey Robbinsville is a census-designated place (CDP) located within Robbinsville Township (known as Washington Township until 2007) in Mercer County, New Jersey, United States. The area is served as United States Postal Service", "19th best place to live in its 2008 rankings of the "Best Places To Live" in New Jersey. According to the United States Census Bureau, the borough had a total area of 8.438 square miles (21.855 km), including 8.202 square miles (21.243 km) of land and 0.236 square miles (0.612 km) of water (2.80%). Unincorporated communities, localities and place names located partially or completely within the borough include Penny Pot. The borough is one of 56 South Jersey municipalities that are included within the New Jersey Pinelands National Reserve, a protected natural area of unique ecology covering , that has"]], "steps": [{"stage": "router", "label": "SINGLE_HOP", "raw": "SINGLE_HOP 

